arch:property.oc:show_val: Early 20th century deposits(0-40cm)underlain by St. Johns IIa deposit(40-60cmbs)underlain by Taylor deposits(60-100cmbs). Diagnostic artifacts from all occupations recovered.

Based on Brockington data, prehistoric camp site possibly utilized from the Middle/Late Archaic (ca. 3,000 to 500 BC) through Middle Woodland-Early Mississippian (500 BC to AD 1200) periods with an early 20th century historic component.
